{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741819949,"sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_SsOzAx6QtvTQxburpNJC5183","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 20,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n7:   \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n8:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n9:   \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n10:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n11:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n12:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n13:   \"lineage\": {\n14:     \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n15:     \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n16:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n17:     \"generation\": 1,\n18:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n19:   },\n20:   \"fanout\": {\n21:     \"executors\": [\n22:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 },\n23:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 }\n24:     ],\n25:     \"concurrency\": 2\n26:   }\n27: }\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"maxIterations\": 20,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"maxIterations\": 20,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {\n    \"executors\": [\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 }\n    ],\n    \"concurrency\": 2\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":27,"totalLines":27,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1780741819942,"end":1780741819948}},"id":"prt_e9c7bcb15001ROdtEwM6eeFSUU","sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","messageID":"msg_e9c7bbd43001lI9F5R2DGfLXpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741820633,"sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_E4JFvLSeRay3bBYprlq63804","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Resolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n6: \n7: ## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n8: \n9: - Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n10: - Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n11: \n12: ## Exclusion\n13: \n14: Do NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n15: \n16: ## Done-Definition\n17: \n18: Every key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n19: - **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n20: - **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb\n21: - **ACCEPTED** — risk consciously accepted with explicit rationale\n22: - **DEFERRED** — blocked on a named external dependency\n23: \n24: Unclassified = not done. Add newly discovered risks as new key questions; they need terminal classification too.\n25: \n26: ## Key Questions\n27: \n28: - [ ] RQ1: Daemon-bypass enforcement — public CLI provably IPC-only? Admin direct-DB path inventory; unix-socket trust model + socket permissions.\n29: - [ ] RQ2: Schema-drift mechanics — all 37 arg shapes round-trip via argv + `--json`? Codegen feasibility from TOOL_DEFINITIONS; tools that don't map cleanly.\n30: - [ ] RQ3: Lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn vs MCP-owned daemon; simultaneous CLI spawns; CLI-spawned daemon lifetime/reaping/orphan risk (six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers observed today).\n31: - [ ] RQ4: Retryable taxonomy — complete error→exit map (-32001, cold-start, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; 75 vs 69).\n32: - [ ] RQ5: Hook latency budget — daemon-down cold path (auto-spawn + 15–30s embedder warm) vs per-runtime hook timeout ceilings; which hook types can shell out.\n33: - [ ] RQ6: Per-call spawn overhead — MEASURE node startup + socket round-trip on this host; validate the 50–150ms estimate.\n34: - [ ] RQ7: Session-identity semantics — sessionId propagation verified in dedup/learning/working-memory code paths; what non-codex runtimes pass.\n35: - [ ] RQ8: Build/activation drift — shim→dist staleness; launcher bootstrap-lock coverage of the CLI handoff.\n36: - [ ] RQ9: Dual-client load — MCP+CLI simultaneous traffic contention; existing stress-test coverage vs gaps.\n37: - [ ] RQ10: Effort reconciliation — one defensible dual-stack estimate (8–12d vs 13–16d vs 3–4wk).\n38: - [ ] RQ11: Platform/socket constraints — macOS sun_path limit handling; Windows non-goal decision.\n39: \n40: ## Known Context\n41: \n42: - The daemon IPC bridge serves multiple concurrent clients (test-proven); owner lease is the single-writer boundary.\n43: - `generate-context.js` performed a full indexed save with the MCP down on 2026-06-06 (CLI-path precedent).\n44: - The 2026-06-06 disconnect incident: owner-exit left the daemon down; Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session.\n45: - Read-only bash timing measurements are permitted; file mutation is not.\n46: \n47: ## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n48: \n49: - Pure per-invocation CLI (run 1); MCP removal (non-goal — dual-stack).\n50: \n51: ## Next Focus\n52: \n53: Iteration 1: RQ1 + RQ3 (the two HIGH-severity structural risks). Then proceed by severity, adding discovered risks as new RQs.\n54: \n55: ## Parameters\n56: \n57: - Max iterations: 20 per lane (terminal cap)\n58: - Convergence threshold: 0.05 (genuine convergence active; all-questions-classified is the intended exit)\n\n(End of file - total 58 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n\n## Topic\n\nResolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n\n## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n\n- Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n- Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n\n## Exclusion\n\nDo NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n\n## Done-Definition\n\nEvery key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n- **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n- **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n\n## Topic\n\nResolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n\n## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n\n- Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n- Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n\n## Exclusion\n\nDo NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n\n## Done-Definition\n\nEvery key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n- **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n- **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb\n- **ACCEPTED** — risk consciously accepted with explicit rationale\n- **DEFERRED** — blocked on a named external dependency\n\nUnclassified = not done. Add newly discovered risks as new key questions; they need terminal classification too.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] RQ1: Daemon-bypass enforcement — public CLI provably IPC-only? Admin direct-DB path inventory; unix-socket trust model + socket permissions.\n- [ ] RQ2: Schema-drift mechanics — all 37 arg shapes round-trip via argv + `--json`? Codegen feasibility from TOOL_DEFINITIONS; tools that don't map cleanly.\n- [ ] RQ3: Lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn vs MCP-owned daemon; simultaneous CLI spawns; CLI-spawned daemon lifetime/reaping/orphan risk (six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers observed today).\n- [ ] RQ4: Retryable taxonomy — complete error→exit map (-32001, cold-start, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; 75 vs 69).\n- [ ] RQ5: Hook latency budget — daemon-down cold path (auto-spawn + 15–30s embedder warm) vs per-runtime hook timeout ceilings; which hook types can shell out.\n- [ ] RQ6: Per-call spawn overhead — MEASURE node startup + socket round-trip on this host; validate the 50–150ms estimate.\n- [ ] RQ7: Session-identity semantics — sessionId propagation verified in dedup/learning/working-memory code paths; what non-codex runtimes pass.\n- [ ] RQ8: Build/activation drift — shim→dist staleness; launcher bootstrap-lock coverage of the CLI handoff.\n- [ ] RQ9: Dual-client load — MCP+CLI simultaneous traffic contention; existing stress-test coverage vs gaps.\n- [ ] RQ10: Effort reconciliation — one defensible dual-stack estimate (8–12d vs 13–16d vs 3–4wk).\n- [ ] RQ11: Platform/socket constraints — macOS sun_path limit handling; Windows non-goal decision.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- The daemon IPC bridge serves multiple concurrent clients (test-proven); owner lease is the single-writer boundary.\n- `generate-context.js` performed a full indexed save with the MCP down on 2026-06-06 (CLI-path precedent).\n- The 2026-06-06 disconnect incident: owner-exit left the daemon down; Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session.\n- Read-only bash timing measurements are permitted; file mutation is not.\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- Pure per-invocation CLI (run 1); MCP removal (non-goal — dual-stack).\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 1: RQ1 + RQ3 (the two HIGH-severity structural risks). Then proceed by severity, adding discovered risks as new RQs.\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 20 per lane (terminal cap)\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (genuine convergence active; all-questions-classified is the intended exit)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":58,"totalLines":58,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780741820622,"end":1780741820632}},"id":"prt_e9c7bce89001Nosum3PIEfvzzs","sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","messageID":"msg_e9c7bbd43001lI9F5R2DGfLXpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741821359,"sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_Gw1fGJcIIT90KXu7KeeF9651","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Run 3: risk resolution before dual-stack CLI implementation — 11-RQ seed register, done-definition RESOLVED/MITIGATED/ACCEPTED/DEFERRED, convergence-driven cap 20.\",\"maxIterations\":20,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":false},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek-risk\",\"mimo-risk\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":20,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\"parentSessionId\":\"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Run 3: risk resolution before dual-stack CLI implementation — 11-RQ seed register, done-definition RESOLVED/MITIGATED/ACCEPTED/DEFERRED, convergence-driven cap 20.\",\"maxIterations\":20,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":false},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek-risk\",\"mimo-risk\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":20,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\"parentSessionId\":\"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Run 3: risk resolution before dual-stack CLI implementation — 11-RQ seed register, done-definition RESOLVED/MITIGATED/ACCEPTED/DEFERRED, convergence-driven cap 20.\",\"maxIterations\":20,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":false},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek-risk\",\"mimo-risk\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":20,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\"parentSessionId\":\"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1780741821352,"end":1780741821358}},"id":"prt_e9c7bd12e0015p9nZ3AWeFJ4Tl","sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","messageID":"msg_e9c7bbd43001lI9F5R2DGfLXpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741822042,"sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_JPHKsLFkEnLDEl8J9yU31099","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/orchestration-status.log"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/orchestration-status.log</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"deepseek-risk\",\"index\":0,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.330Z\"}\n2: {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"mimo-risk\",\"index\":1,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.334Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"deepseek-risk\",\"index\":0,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.330Z\"}\n{\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"mimo-risk\",\"index\":1,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.334Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/orchestration-status.log","text":"{\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"deepseek-risk\",\"index\":0,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.330Z\"}\n{\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"mimo-risk\",\"index\":1,\"at\":\"2026-06-06T10:29:41.334Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/orchestration-status.log","time":{"start":1780741822034,"end":1780741822040}},"id":"prt_e9c7bd40b001lftO0Y68vj27mc","sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","messageID":"msg_e9c7bbd43001lI9F5R2DGfLXpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741822717,"sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_7PqIyynS5tPBHr8qGT5w3313","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/research.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research: Memory MCP → CLI Feasibility (Merged Synthesis)\n2: \n3: - **Date:** 2026-06-06 · **Session:** `dr-20260606T105055-fanout028` · **Mode:** 3-lane heterogeneous fan-out, forced 5 iterations per lane\n4: - **Lanes:** deepseek (deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro, 9.6 min), minimax (minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3, 40.7 min), mimo (xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, 6.6 min) — all via cli-opencode, reasoning high\n5: - **Outcome:** 3/3 lanes succeeded, 15/15 iterations, 5/5 KQs answered per lane with file:line evidence\n6: - **Per-lane reports:** `lineages/{deepseek,minimax,mimo}/research.md` · merged registry: `deep-research-findings-registry.json` · attribution: `fanout-attribution.md`\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## 1. Verdict\n11: \n12: **YES — the mk-spec-memory MCP can be replaced by a CLI with zero feature loss, but ONLY if the daemon stays.** All three lanes independently confirmed: the MCP *protocol* layer (stdio transport, tool schemas, negotiation) provides no unique functionality — the daemon already speaks JSON-RPC over `daemon-ipc.sock`, and a CLI can drive the identical handler surface through the identical socket.\n13: \n14: **Architecture decision — GO with (b)+auto-spawn (= a thin (c)):**\n15: \n16: - All lanes: **(a) pure per-invocation CLI FAILS the zero-feature-loss bar** (loses the watcher, warm embedder, async queues, session state — 5–6 tools degraded, 3–5 services lost).\n17: - All lanes: **(b) CLI over the existing daemon meets the bar exactly** — every tool, service, and affordance preserved; nothing about the daemon changes.\n18: - Lane split on (b) vs (c): DeepSeek + MiMo recommend (b) plain (\"the crash-loop guard already restarts crashes\"); MiniMax recommends (c) (\"auto-spawn is what actually prevents the 2026-06-06 incident class\"). **Adjudication: MiniMax is right about the incident mode** — the crash-loop guard restarts a crashed *child*, but when the daemon's owner session exits cleanly the daemon goes away by design and nothing revives it until a new launcher connects. A CLI whose connect path falls back to spawning the launcher (exactly what every MCP client connect already does) closes that gap at ~1 day of marginal effort. (c) here is not a new architecture; it is (b) with the existing launcher used as the spawn path.\n19: \n20: **Effort:** ~3 weeks center estimate (MiniMax: 13–16 days · DeepSeek/MiMo: 3–4 weeks). The CLI itself is a thin IPC adapter (~1,000 LOC). **Critical path (unanimous): OpenCode runtime support for registered shell tools with per-subcommand permission gating** — the only dependency outside this repo; mitigable with a 2–3 day CLI shim (MiniMax) or interim bare-shell allowlisting (DeepSeek/MiMo).\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## 2. KQ1 — 37-Tool Parity Matrix (consolidated)\n25: \n26: All 37 tools have CLI equivalents; **zero tools are MCP-only.** Consensus classification (lanes diverged only on `memory_ingest_start`):\n27: \n28: | Class | Count (DeepSeek) | Count (MiMo) | Meaning |\n29: |---|---|---|---|\n30: | STATELESS | 22 | 22 | Pure DB read/write — trivially CLI-portable, daemon-free |\n31: | STATE-EMBED | 10 | 9 | Needs embedding generation — portable with cold-embed latency (~100–500 ms) unless daemon keeps the embedder warm |\n32: | STATE-WATCHER | 5 | 6 | Needs daemon-resident state (session context, job-queue process, watcher): `memory_ingest_status`, `memory_ingest_cancel`, `session_health`, `session_resume`, `session_bootstrap` (+ MiMo: `memory_ingest_start` async path) |\n33: | MCP-ONLY | **0** | **0** | — |\n34: \n35: MiniMax's complementary lens: **24/37 daemon-free, 13/37 soft-dependent, 0 hard-required in handler terms**, and **5 tools already have CLI ports today** (`generate-context.js` save; `cli.ts` stats/bulk-delete; `reindex-embeddings.js`; `validate-memory-quality.js`). Full 37-row tables: `lineages/deepseek/research.md` §3, `lineages/mimo/research.md` §3, `lineages/minimax/iterations/iteration-001.md`.\n36: \n37: Proposed CLI shape (converged across lanes): `spec-memory <subcommand> --flags` (e.g. `spec-memory search --query \"...\" --limit 10`, `spec-memory session-bootstrap`, `spec-memory list-tools --format json`).\n38: \n39: ## 3. KQ2 — Daemon-Dependency Loss Table (consolidated)\n40: \n41: | Service | (a) pure CLI | (b) CLI-over-daemon | (c) + auto-spawn |\n42: |---|---|---|---|\n43: | Warm embedder (ollama→hf→OpenAI→Voyage; 15–30 s cold start) | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (cold on spawn) |\n44: | Chokidar file-watcher reindex | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (gap on restart) |\n45: | Async embedding retry queue + enrichment drain | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (backlog on restart) |\n46: | Async ingest job queue (process) | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT |\n47: | RSS watchdog + crash-loop reap | **LOST/N-A** | KEPT | KEPT |\n48: | Session context (working memory, attention decay, dedup ~50% token savings, constitutional priming) | **LOST/ADAPTED** | KEPT | KEPT (brief loss on recycle) |\n49: | FTS5 auto-heal, transaction recovery, shadow eval logging | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT |\n50: \n51: MiniMax negative-knowledge corrections (verified, adopted): **the single-writer lease is NOT daemon-resident** (interprocess mkdir lock by design) and **warm session briefs are NOT a RAM cache** (per-session SQLite rows) — both survive even architecture (a). This trims the true daemon-hard set to: warm embedder, watcher, queues/watchdog process, and live job/session processes.\n52: \n53: **Tool availability:** (a) 31–32/37 → FAIL · (b) 37/37 → PASS · (c) 37/37 → PASS.\n54: \n55: ## 4. KQ3 — MCP-Only Affordances and Replacements\n56: \n57: | Affordance | Replacement | Status |\n58: |---|---|---|\n59: | Tool-schema auto-discovery | `spec-memory list-tools --format json` (static manifest) + per-runtime `tools:`/allowlist registration | Ported |\n60: | Per-tool runtime permissioning | Per-runtime: OpenCode `tools:` block / Claude Bash allowlist patterns / Codex `--approval-policy` / permissions-matrix.json | Ported (runtime-side work) |\n61: | Zod boundary validation | Same Zod schema modules at the argv layer | Ported (reused) |\n62: | `-32001` retryable + session-proxy replay | (b)/(c): existing proxy unchanged; (a): POSIX exit 75 EX_TEMPFAIL + client retry | Ported/Preserved |\n63: | Auto-surface hooks / session priming | (b)/(c): daemon keeps running them; (a): **LOST** — explicit `spec-memory session-bootstrap` call required | Architecture-dependent |\n64: | MCP per-session schema token overhead | Eliminated entirely | **NET GAIN** |\n65: \n66: ## 5. KQ4 — Integration-Surface Migration Map\n67: \n68: Converged inventory: **~28–29 files, ~120–125 references.**\n69: \n70: | Surface | Files | Refs | Effort | Risk |\n71: |---|---|---|---|---|\n72: | Agent allowed-tools (6 agent .md) | 6 | ~6–20 | <1 h | Low |\n73: | Command YAML/markdown (memory/*, doctor/*, deep/*) | 16–19 | ~80–106 | 3–4 days (inline tool calls need CLI flag-syntax rewrite, not bare search-replace — MiniMax) | Low |\n74: | **OpenCode runtime config (`opencode.json` `tools:` block)** | 1 | ~6 | **1–3 weeks (THE gate)** or 2–3 day CLI shim | **HIGH** |\n75: | Runtime hooks / session priming / AGENTS.md | 2 | ~6 | <1 day | Medium |\n76: | Doctor scripts (`mcp-doctor.sh`) | 1 | ~6 | ~1 h | Low |\n77: | Deep-loop allowed-tools | 4 | ~10 | Low | Low |\n78: \n79: ## 6. KQ5 — Architecture Comparison and Scores\n80: \n81: | Criterion | (a) | (b) | (c) |\n82: |---|---|---|---|\n83: | Tools preserved | 31–32/37 | 37/37 | 37/37 |\n84: | Daemon services preserved | ~4/13 | all | all |\n85: | Protocol affordances | loses auto-surface | all | all |\n86: | Effort | ~60 h | ~85 h / 3–4 wk | +~1 day over (b) |\n87: | Operational risk (incident class of 2026-06-06) | HIGH | LOW (daemon-down-until-demand remains) | LOWEST (auto-spawn closes it) |\n88: | MiniMax weighted score | 0.45 | 0.92 | **0.97** |\n89: | Zero feature loss? | **NO** | **YES** | **YES** |\n90: \n91: **Merged recommendation: GO — build the CLI over the existing daemon/IPC socket, with connect-falls-back-to-spawn.** Keep launcher, IPC bridge, session proxy, context-server, and all 37 handlers unchanged. Ship behind a feature flag (default OFF), run dual-stack (MCP + CLI) for a deprecation window, then remove the MCP registration. Rollback is a 1–2 day revert (re-add the registration).\n92: \n93: ## 7. Consolidated Risk Register\n94: \n95: | # | Risk | Sev | Arch | Mitigation |\n96: |---|---|---|---|---|\n97: | R1 | OpenCode lacks shell-tool permission gating (the gate) | HIGH | all | Feature request + 2–3 day CLI shim; interim Bash allowlisting |\n98: | R2 | Daemon down until demand (owner exit) | MED | (b) | Auto-spawn fallback (adopting (c) retires this) |\n99: | R3 | Cold-embed latency / timeouts | MED | (a) | N/A under (b)/(c) |\n100: | R4 | Migration regressions (~125 refs incl. inline prompt-body tool calls) | LOW-MED | all | Phased migration, tests, dual-stack window |\n101: | R5 | Stale search from watcher loss | MED | (a) | N/A under (b)/(c) |\n102: | R6 | Concurrent CLI writers | LOW | (a) | WAL + existing interprocess locks (lease survives all archs) |\n103: | R7 | Rollback risk | LOW | (b)/(c) | Feature flag, MCP registration revert |\n104: \n105: ## 8. Negative Knowledge (ruled out, with attribution)\n106: \n107: - Pure CLI (a) as the answer — fails the bar (all lanes).\n108: - Plain (c)-as-separate-architecture and plain (b)-without-spawn — collapsed into (b)+auto-spawn (orchestrator adjudication of the lane split).\n109: - \"11 maintenance CLIs ≈ broad parity evidence\" — 10/11 are operational utilities, not tool substitutes (MiniMax).\n110: - Single-writer lease / warm briefs as daemon-resident — interprocess mkdir lock / SQLite rows by design (MiniMax).\n111: - Single-binary CLI framing — the system stays multi-process; the CLI is one entry point (MiniMax).\n112: - Atomic migration — composable per-tool/per-runtime; only the OpenCode `tools:` gate is atomic (MiniMax).\n113: - KQ1 parity alone as a zero-loss verdict — affordances (KQ3) had to be evaluated separately (MiniMax).\n114: \n115: ## 9. Implementation Sequencing (if accepted — MiniMax plan, adjusted)\n116: \n117: | Phase | Work | Duration |\n118: |---|---|---|\n119: | 1 | CLI front-end: 37 subcommands + connect/spawn path over `daemon-ipc.sock` | ~5 days |\n120: | 2 | Mechanical migration: agents, command YAMLs, AGENTS.md, doctor scripts (~125 refs) | 3–4 days |\n121: | 3 | OpenCode runtime `tools:` gate (or CLI shim) | 2–3 days (shim) / 1–3 wk (upstream) |\n122: | 4 | Auto-spawn fallback + \"MCP\"→\"IPC\" naming hygiene | 1–2 days |\n123: | 5 | Test + verify; ship behind feature flag (default OFF) | 2–3 days |\n124: | 6 | Dual-stack monitoring window → default ON → remove MCP registration | 1–2 weeks elapsed |\n125: \n126: ## 10. Lineage Attribution and Independence\n127: \n128: | Lane | Verdict | Independence | Distinct contributions |\n129: |---|---|---|---|\n130: | deepseek | GO (b) | **Independent** (ran first, concurrent with minimax) | 3-class tool taxonomy; 13-service loss table; affordance ports incl. EX_TEMPFAIL mapping; risk register |\n131: | minimax | GO (c) | **Independent** (concurrent with deepseek) | 5 already-ported tools; lease/briefs debunks; per-runtime affordance matrix; S3 gate + shim; weighted scoring; sequencing plan; incident-mode argument for auto-spawn |\n132: | mimo | GO (b) | **DeepSeek-informed** — its report explicitly compares to \"the DeepSeek lane\" (it read the sibling lineage dir; no read-exclusion was configured for sibling lanes). Treated as verification + refinement of deepseek, not independent replication | `ingest_start` reclassification (STATE-EMBED→async caveat → 6 STATE-WATCHER); independent citation re-verification |\n133: \n134: Methodological note for future fan-outs: sequentially-pooled lanes can read earlier lanes' outputs unless lineage dirs are excluded in the prompt — concurrency ≠ isolation. (Consistent with the 018 fan-out-diversity experiment: heterogeneity's value here was exactly adjudication — the (b)-vs-(c) split and MiniMax's debunks — not raw coverage.)\n135: \n136: ## 11. Convergence Report (merged)\n137: \n138: | Lane | Iterations | Stop reason | KQs | newInfoRatio trend |\n139: |---|---|---|---|---|\n140: | deepseek | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached | 5/5 | flat 1.0 (orthogonal KQ-per-iteration design) |\n141: | minimax | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached + all-questions-answered | 5/5 | 0.95→0.50 (rolling avg 0.66) |\n142: | mimo | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached | 5/5 | flat 1.0 |\n143: \n144: Forced-5 design held: no lane stopped early; convergence threshold 0 at root, terminal caps per lane.\n145: \n146: ## 12. Run 2 — CLI Back-End Design for Dual-Stack (2026-06-06)\n147: \n148: Follow-up run per operator direction: 1 lane (cli-codex, `gpt-5.5`, reasoning xhigh, service tier fast), 3 forced iterations, 7.8 min, premise = this document's GO verdict. Full design: `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`.\n149: \n150: **Design verdict:** build `spec-memory` as a daemon-backed dual-stack surface — compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts` behind a stable `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim. The CLI is just another IPC client: it reuses `getIpcSocketPath()` from the bridge, auto-spawns via `mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` on ENOENT/dead socket, **generates its 37 subcommands from the canonical `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`** (schema drift impossible by construction) with the existing Zod `validateToolArgs` at the argv boundary, renders `--format json|text|jsonl` (JSON canonical), and maps exits 0/1/64/69/**75 (retryable, incl. `-32001`)**.\n151: \n152: **Coexistence (proven, not assumed):** the IPC bridge already serves multiple concurrent clients (existing vitest evidence); the owner lease stays the single-writer boundary; session continuity via `--session-id` forwarded into tool args (server already resolves identity from args/transport/`CODEX_THREAD_ID`). Non-goals locked: MCP registration stays, no migration of the ~125 references, no daemon bypass.\n153: \n154: **Delivery:** 8 file-level changes (shim, CLI, generated manifest, package bin, 3 test suites incl. an all-37 parity extension and a dual-client MCP+CLI test, runtime allowlist `Bash(node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs *)`), risk register topped by daemon-bypass and schema-drift (both mitigated structurally). **Effort: 8–12 engineering days.**\n155: \n156: <!-- ANCHOR:sources -->\n157: ## Sources\n158: \n159: - Per-lane syntheses: `lineages/deepseek/research.md`, `lineages/minimax/research.md`, `lineages/mimo/research.md` (each citing 30+ file:line anchors across `mcp_server/tools/*`, `mcp_server/handlers/*`, `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-{ipc-bridge,session-proxy}.cjs`, `opencode.json`, agents/commands/doctor surfaces).\n160: - Per-iteration evidence: `lineages/*/iterations/iteration-00{1..5}.md` (15 files).\n161: - Merged findings registry: `deep-research-findings-registry.json` (18 findings, minimax registry; deepseek/mimo findings carried in their research.md syntheses — registry coverage 1/3 lanes noted in `fanout-attribution.md`).\n162: - Orchestration: `orchestration-summary.json` (3/3 succeeded), `orchestration-status.log`.\n163: - Run 2 (CLI back-end design): `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md` + `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/iterations/iteration-00{1..3}.md` + registry; orchestration: `cli-backend/orchestration-summary.json` (1/1 succeeded).\n164: <!-- /ANCHOR:sources -->\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research: Memory MCP → CLI Feasibility (Merged Synthesis)\n\n- **Date:** 2026-06-06 · **Session:** `dr-20260606T105055-fanout028` · **Mode:** 3-lane heterogeneous fan-out, forced 5 iterations per lane\n- **Lanes:** deepseek (deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro, 9.6 min), minimax (minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3, 40.7 min), mimo (xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, 6.6 min) — all via cli-opencode, reasoning high\n- **Outcome:** 3/3 lanes succeeded, 15/15 iterations, 5/5 KQs answered per lane with file:line evidence\n- **Per-lane reports:** `lineages/{deepseek,minimax,mimo}/research.md` · merged registry: `deep-research-findings-registry.json` · attribution: `fanout-attribution.md`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Verdict\n\n**YES — the mk-spec-memory MCP can be replaced by a CLI with zero feature loss, but ONLY if the daemon stays.** All three lanes independently confirmed: the MCP *protocol* layer (stdio transport, tool schemas, negotiation) provides no unique functionality — the daemon already speaks JSON-RPC over `daemon-ipc.sock`, and a CLI can drive the identical handler surface through the identical socket.\n\n**Architecture decision — GO with (b)+auto-spawn (= a thin (c)):**\n\n- All lanes: **(a) pure per-invocation CLI FAILS the zero-feature-loss bar** (loses the watcher, warm embedder, async queues, session state — 5–6 tools degraded, 3–5 services lost).\n- All lanes: **(b) CLI over the existing daemon meets the bar exactly** — every tool, service, and affordance preserved; nothing about the daemon changes.\n- Lane split on (b) vs (c): DeepSeek + MiMo recommend (b) plain (\"the crash-loop guard already restarts crashes\"); MiniMax recommends (c) (\"auto-spawn is what actually prevents the 2026-06-06 incident class\"). **Adjudication: MiniMax is right about the incident mode** — the crash-loop guard restarts a crashed *child*, but when the daemon's owner session exits cleanly the daemon goes away by design and nothing revives it until a new launcher connects. A CLI whose connect path falls back to spawning the launcher (exactly what every MCP client connect already does) closes that gap at ~1 day of marginal effort. (c) here is not a new architecture; it is (b) with the existing launcher used as the spawn path.\n\n**Effort:** ~3 weeks center estimate (MiniMax: 13–16 days · DeepSeek/MiMo: 3–4 weeks). The CLI itself is a thin IPC adapter (~1,000 LOC). **Critical path (unanimous): OpenCode runtime support for registered shell tools with per-subcommand permission gating** — the only dependency outside this repo; mitigable with a 2–3 day CLI shim (MiniMax) or interim bare-shell allowlisting (DeepSeek/MiMo).","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/research.md","text":"# Deep Research: Memory MCP → CLI Feasibility (Merged Synthesis)\n\n- **Date:** 2026-06-06 · **Session:** `dr-20260606T105055-fanout028` · **Mode:** 3-lane heterogeneous fan-out, forced 5 iterations per lane\n- **Lanes:** deepseek (deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro, 9.6 min), minimax (minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3, 40.7 min), mimo (xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, 6.6 min) — all via cli-opencode, reasoning high\n- **Outcome:** 3/3 lanes succeeded, 15/15 iterations, 5/5 KQs answered per lane with file:line evidence\n- **Per-lane reports:** `lineages/{deepseek,minimax,mimo}/research.md` · merged registry: `deep-research-findings-registry.json` · attribution: `fanout-attribution.md`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Verdict\n\n**YES — the mk-spec-memory MCP can be replaced by a CLI with zero feature loss, but ONLY if the daemon stays.** All three lanes independently confirmed: the MCP *protocol* layer (stdio transport, tool schemas, negotiation) provides no unique functionality — the daemon already speaks JSON-RPC over `daemon-ipc.sock`, and a CLI can drive the identical handler surface through the identical socket.\n\n**Architecture decision — GO with (b)+auto-spawn (= a thin (c)):**\n\n- All lanes: **(a) pure per-invocation CLI FAILS the zero-feature-loss bar** (loses the watcher, warm embedder, async queues, session state — 5–6 tools degraded, 3–5 services lost).\n- All lanes: **(b) CLI over the existing daemon meets the bar exactly** — every tool, service, and affordance preserved; nothing about the daemon changes.\n- Lane split on (b) vs (c): DeepSeek + MiMo recommend (b) plain (\"the crash-loop guard already restarts crashes\"); MiniMax recommends (c) (\"auto-spawn is what actually prevents the 2026-06-06 incident class\"). **Adjudication: MiniMax is right about the incident mode** — the crash-loop guard restarts a crashed *child*, but when the daemon's owner session exits cleanly the daemon goes away by design and nothing revives it until a new launcher connects. A CLI whose connect path falls back to spawning the launcher (exactly what every MCP client connect already does) closes that gap at ~1 day of marginal effort. (c) here is not a new architecture; it is (b) with the existing launcher used as the spawn path.\n\n**Effort:** ~3 weeks center estimate (MiniMax: 13–16 days · DeepSeek/MiMo: 3–4 weeks). The CLI itself is a thin IPC adapter (~1,000 LOC). **Critical path (unanimous): OpenCode runtime support for registered shell tools with per-subcommand permission gating** — the only dependency outside this repo; mitigable with a 2–3 day CLI shim (MiniMax) or interim bare-shell allowlisting (DeepSeek/MiMo).\n\n---\n\n## 2. KQ1 — 37-Tool Parity Matrix (consolidated)\n\nAll 37 tools have CLI equivalents; **zero tools are MCP-only.** Consensus classification (lanes diverged only on `memory_ingest_start`):\n\n| Class | Count (DeepSeek) | Count (MiMo) | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| STATELESS | 22 | 22 | Pure DB read/write — trivially CLI-portable, daemon-free |\n| STATE-EMBED | 10 | 9 | Needs embedding generation — portable with cold-embed latency (~100–500 ms) unless daemon keeps the embedder warm |\n| STATE-WATCHER | 5 | 6 | Needs daemon-resident state (session context, job-queue process, watcher): `memory_ingest_status`, `memory_ingest_cancel`, `session_health`, `session_resume`, `session_bootstrap` (+ MiMo: `memory_ingest_start` async path) |\n| MCP-ONLY | **0** | **0** | — |\n\nMiniMax's complementary lens: **24/37 daemon-free, 13/37 soft-dependent, 0 hard-required in handler terms**, and **5 tools already have CLI ports today** (`generate-context.js` save; `cli.ts` stats/bulk-delete; `reindex-embeddings.js`; `validate-memory-quality.js`). Full 37-row tables: `lineages/deepseek/research.md` §3, `lineages/mimo/research.md` §3, `lineages/minimax/iterations/iteration-001.md`.\n\nProposed CLI shape (converged across lanes): `spec-memory <subcommand> --flags` (e.g. `spec-memory search --query \"...\" --limit 10`, `spec-memory session-bootstrap`, `spec-memory list-tools --format json`).\n\n## 3. KQ2 — Daemon-Dependency Loss Table (consolidated)\n\n| Service | (a) pure CLI | (b) CLI-over-daemon | (c) + auto-spawn |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Warm embedder (ollama→hf→OpenAI→Voyage; 15–30 s cold start) | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (cold on spawn) |\n| Chokidar file-watcher reindex | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (gap on restart) |\n| Async embedding retry queue + enrichment drain | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT (backlog on restart) |\n| Async ingest job queue (process) | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT |\n| RSS watchdog + crash-loop reap | **LOST/N-A** | KEPT | KEPT |\n| Session context (working memory, attention decay, dedup ~50% token savings, constitutional priming) | **LOST/ADAPTED** | KEPT | KEPT (brief loss on recycle) |\n| FTS5 auto-heal, transaction recovery, shadow eval logging | **LOST** | KEPT | KEPT |\n\nMiniMax negative-knowledge corrections (verified, adopted): **the single-writer lease is NOT daemon-resident** (interprocess mkdir lock by design) and **warm session briefs are NOT a RAM cache** (per-session SQLite rows) — both survive even architecture (a). This trims the true daemon-hard set to: warm embedder, watcher, queues/watchdog process, and live job/session processes.\n\n**Tool availability:** (a) 31–32/37 → FAIL · (b) 37/37 → PASS · (c) 37/37 → PASS.\n\n## 4. KQ3 — MCP-Only Affordances and Replacements\n\n| Affordance | Replacement | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| Tool-schema auto-discovery | `spec-memory list-tools --format json` (static manifest) + per-runtime `tools:`/allowlist registration | Ported |\n| Per-tool runtime permissioning | Per-runtime: OpenCode `tools:` block / Claude Bash allowlist patterns / Codex `--approval-policy` / permissions-matrix.json | Ported (runtime-side work) |\n| Zod boundary validation | Same Zod schema modules at the argv layer | Ported (reused) |\n| `-32001` retryable + session-proxy replay | (b)/(c): existing proxy unchanged; (a): POSIX exit 75 EX_TEMPFAIL + client retry | Ported/Preserved |\n| Auto-surface hooks / session priming | (b)/(c): daemon keeps running them; (a): **LOST** — explicit `spec-memory session-bootstrap` call required | Architecture-dependent |\n| MCP per-session schema token overhead | Eliminated entirely | **NET GAIN** |\n\n## 5. KQ4 — Integration-Surface Migration Map\n\nConverged inventory: **~28–29 files, ~120–125 references.**\n\n| Surface | Files | Refs | Effort | Risk |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Agent allowed-tools (6 agent .md) | 6 | ~6–20 | <1 h | Low |\n| Command YAML/markdown (memory/*, doctor/*, deep/*) | 16–19 | ~80–106 | 3–4 days (inline tool calls need CLI flag-syntax rewrite, not bare search-replace — MiniMax) | Low |\n| **OpenCode runtime config (`opencode.json` `tools:` block)** | 1 | ~6 | **1–3 weeks (THE gate)** or 2–3 day CLI shim | **HIGH** |\n| Runtime hooks / session priming / AGENTS.md | 2 | ~6 | <1 day | Medium |\n| Doctor scripts (`mcp-doctor.sh`) | 1 | ~6 | ~1 h | Low |\n| Deep-loop allowed-tools | 4 | ~10 | Low | Low |\n\n## 6. KQ5 — Architecture Comparison and Scores\n\n| Criterion | (a) | (b) | (c) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Tools preserved | 31–32/37 | 37/37 | 37/37 |\n| Daemon services preserved | ~4/13 | all | all |\n| Protocol affordances | loses auto-surface | all | all |\n| Effort | ~60 h | ~85 h / 3–4 wk | +~1 day over (b) |\n| Operational risk (incident class of 2026-06-06) | HIGH | LOW (daemon-down-until-demand remains) | LOWEST (auto-spawn closes it) |\n| MiniMax weighted score | 0.45 | 0.92 | **0.97** |\n| Zero feature loss? | **NO** | **YES** | **YES** |\n\n**Merged recommendation: GO — build the CLI over the existing daemon/IPC socket, with connect-falls-back-to-spawn.** Keep launcher, IPC bridge, session proxy, context-server, and all 37 handlers unchanged. Ship behind a feature flag (default OFF), run dual-stack (MCP + CLI) for a deprecation window, then remove the MCP registration. Rollback is a 1–2 day revert (re-add the registration).\n\n## 7. Consolidated Risk Register\n\n| # | Risk | Sev | Arch | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| R1 | OpenCode lacks shell-tool permission gating (the gate) | HIGH | all | Feature request + 2–3 day CLI shim; interim Bash allowlisting |\n| R2 | Daemon down until demand (owner exit) | MED | (b) | Auto-spawn fallback (adopting (c) retires this) |\n| R3 | Cold-embed latency / timeouts | MED | (a) | N/A under (b)/(c) |\n| R4 | Migration regressions (~125 refs incl. inline prompt-body tool calls) | LOW-MED | all | Phased migration, tests, dual-stack window |\n| R5 | Stale search from watcher loss | MED | (a) | N/A under (b)/(c) |\n| R6 | Concurrent CLI writers | LOW | (a) | WAL + existing interprocess locks (lease survives all archs) |\n| R7 | Rollback risk | LOW | (b)/(c) | Feature flag, MCP registration revert |\n\n## 8. Negative Knowledge (ruled out, with attribution)\n\n- Pure CLI (a) as the answer — fails the bar (all lanes).\n- Plain (c)-as-separate-architecture and plain (b)-without-spawn — collapsed into (b)+auto-spawn (orchestrator adjudication of the lane split).\n- \"11 maintenance CLIs ≈ broad parity evidence\" — 10/11 are operational utilities, not tool substitutes (MiniMax).\n- Single-writer lease / warm briefs as daemon-resident — interprocess mkdir lock / SQLite rows by design (MiniMax).\n- Single-binary CLI framing — the system stays multi-process; the CLI is one entry point (MiniMax).\n- Atomic migration — composable per-tool/per-runtime; only the OpenCode `tools:` gate is atomic (MiniMax).\n- KQ1 parity alone as a zero-loss verdict — affordances (KQ3) had to be evaluated separately (MiniMax).\n\n## 9. Implementation Sequencing (if accepted — MiniMax plan, adjusted)\n\n| Phase | Work | Duration |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | CLI front-end: 37 subcommands + connect/spawn path over `daemon-ipc.sock` | ~5 days |\n| 2 | Mechanical migration: agents, command YAMLs, AGENTS.md, doctor scripts (~125 refs) | 3–4 days |\n| 3 | OpenCode runtime `tools:` gate (or CLI shim) | 2–3 days (shim) / 1–3 wk (upstream) |\n| 4 | Auto-spawn fallback + \"MCP\"→\"IPC\" naming hygiene | 1–2 days |\n| 5 | Test + verify; ship behind feature flag (default OFF) | 2–3 days |\n| 6 | Dual-stack monitoring window → default ON → remove MCP registration | 1–2 weeks elapsed |\n\n## 10. Lineage Attribution and Independence\n\n| Lane | Verdict | Independence | Distinct contributions |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| deepseek | GO (b) | **Independent** (ran first, concurrent with minimax) | 3-class tool taxonomy; 13-service loss table; affordance ports incl. EX_TEMPFAIL mapping; risk register |\n| minimax | GO (c) | **Independent** (concurrent with deepseek) | 5 already-ported tools; lease/briefs debunks; per-runtime affordance matrix; S3 gate + shim; weighted scoring; sequencing plan; incident-mode argument for auto-spawn |\n| mimo | GO (b) | **DeepSeek-informed** — its report explicitly compares to \"the DeepSeek lane\" (it read the sibling lineage dir; no read-exclusion was configured for sibling lanes). Treated as verification + refinement of deepseek, not independent replication | `ingest_start` reclassification (STATE-EMBED→async caveat → 6 STATE-WATCHER); independent citation re-verification |\n\nMethodological note for future fan-outs: sequentially-pooled lanes can read earlier lanes' outputs unless lineage dirs are excluded in the prompt — concurrency ≠ isolation. (Consistent with the 018 fan-out-diversity experiment: heterogeneity's value here was exactly adjudication — the (b)-vs-(c) split and MiniMax's debunks — not raw coverage.)\n\n## 11. Convergence Report (merged)\n\n| Lane | Iterations | Stop reason | KQs | newInfoRatio trend |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| deepseek | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached | 5/5 | flat 1.0 (orthogonal KQ-per-iteration design) |\n| minimax | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached + all-questions-answered | 5/5 | 0.95→0.50 (rolling avg 0.66) |\n| mimo | 5/5 | maxIterationsReached | 5/5 | flat 1.0 |\n\nForced-5 design held: no lane stopped early; convergence threshold 0 at root, terminal caps per lane.\n\n## 12. Run 2 — CLI Back-End Design for Dual-Stack (2026-06-06)\n\nFollow-up run per operator direction: 1 lane (cli-codex, `gpt-5.5`, reasoning xhigh, service tier fast), 3 forced iterations, 7.8 min, premise = this document's GO verdict. Full design: `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`.\n\n**Design verdict:** build `spec-memory` as a daemon-backed dual-stack surface — compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts` behind a stable `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim. The CLI is just another IPC client: it reuses `getIpcSocketPath()` from the bridge, auto-spawns via `mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` on ENOENT/dead socket, **generates its 37 subcommands from the canonical `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`** (schema drift impossible by construction) with the existing Zod `validateToolArgs` at the argv boundary, renders `--format json|text|jsonl` (JSON canonical), and maps exits 0/1/64/69/**75 (retryable, incl. `-32001`)**.\n\n**Coexistence (proven, not assumed):** the IPC bridge already serves multiple concurrent clients (existing vitest evidence); the owner lease stays the single-writer boundary; session continuity via `--session-id` forwarded into tool args (server already resolves identity from args/transport/`CODEX_THREAD_ID`). Non-goals locked: MCP registration stays, no migration of the ~125 references, no daemon bypass.\n\n**Delivery:** 8 file-level changes (shim, CLI, generated manifest, package bin, 3 test suites incl. an all-37 parity extension and a dual-client MCP+CLI test, runtime allowlist `Bash(node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs *)`), risk register topped by daemon-bypass and schema-drift (both mitigated structurally). **Effort: 8–12 engineering days.**\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:sources -->\n## Sources\n\n- Per-lane syntheses: `lineages/deepseek/research.md`, `lineages/minimax/research.md`, `lineages/mimo/research.md` (each citing 30+ file:line anchors across `mcp_server/tools/*`, `mcp_server/handlers/*`, `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-{ipc-bridge,session-proxy}.cjs`, `opencode.json`, agents/commands/doctor surfaces).\n- Per-iteration evidence: `lineages/*/iterations/iteration-00{1..5}.md` (15 files).\n- Merged findings registry: `deep-research-findings-registry.json` (18 findings, minimax registry; deepseek/mimo findings carried in their research.md syntheses — registry coverage 1/3 lanes noted in `fanout-attribution.md`).\n- Orchestration: `orchestration-summary.json` (3/3 succeeded), `orchestration-status.log`.\n- Run 2 (CLI back-end design): `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md` + `cli-backend/lineages/gpt/iterations/iteration-00{1..3}.md` + registry; orchestration: `cli-backend/orchestration-summary.json` (1/1 succeeded).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:sources -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/research.md","time":{"start":1780741822711,"end":1780741822716}},"id":"prt_e9c7bd6ca001EEUpSUYgNV4Omq","sessionID":"ses_16384c53affe2f7jn8iVrlwqWM","messageID":"msg_e9c7bbd43001lI9F5R2DGfLXpZ"}}
